     6	/**
     7	 * Creates a {@link MemoryClient} - a fully-featured Ethereum development and testing environment.
     8	 *
     9	 * The MemoryClient is an all-in-one solution that combines:
    10	 * - A complete in-memory Ethereum Virtual Machine implementation
    11	 * - Full support for viem's wallet, test, and public actions
    12	 * - TEVM-specific actions for advanced state manipulation and tracing
    13	 * - Automatic handling of JSON-RPC requests through viem's client interface
    14	 *
    15	 * This provides an integrated environment for local Ethereum development with capabilities like:
    16	 * - Executing and debugging smart contracts without deploying to a testnet
    17	 * - Forking from existing networks with state caching for realistic testing
    18	 * - Direct manipulation of blockchain state for complex test scenarios
    19	 * - Complete control over mining and transaction processing
    20	 * - Compatibility with standard Ethereum tooling and libraries
    21	 *
    22	 * @type {import('./CreateMemoryClientFn.js').CreateMemoryClientFn}
    23	 *
    24	 * @example
    25	 * ```typescript
    26	 * import { createMemoryClient, http } from "tevm";
    27	 * import { optimism } from "tevm/common";
